The municipality says water usage is also 142 million litres above its target of 500 million litres of collective water use per day. CAPW TOWN - The City of Cape Town says the first installation of water management devices at water guzzler's properties will begin this week. Currently the city's dam levels are at 27.9%. The municipality says water usage is also 142 million litres above its target of 500 million litres of collective water use per day. The City's Xanthea Limberg said: “If there’s a knock on the door, don’t be surprised if it’s our water inspectors and law enforcement agency coming to inspect your water use. Our high users have received warning notices and we will be forcefully reducing the water use of those who can't justify their high water usage.”